message.content: The likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are "cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CY". This is because the paper deals with cross-lingual question re-ranking in community forums, which involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques such as machine translation, bilingual dictionaries, and cross-language word embeddings. Therefore, "cs.CL" (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves information retrieval (IR) techniques to find relevant questions, which makes "cs.IR" (Information Retrieval) another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses kernel-based and neural network approaches, which fall under "cs.AI" (Artificial Intelligence) and "cs.LG" (Machine Learning) sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with Arabic-English language pair, which is a specific area of interest in "cs.CY" (Computers and Society) sub-category.
